# Authoritative list of required server env vars (security-guide §10).
# Names only — values live in the gitignored .env.
#
# DATABASE_URL: there is no fixed dev default any more. The dev compose port is ephemeral and
# per-worktree (08 §6.1), so a pasted localhost:5432 resolves to whichever OTHER worktree owns
# the port — that is testing-guide T-14d. Ask for your own:
#   pnpm db:up && pnpm db:url          # -> postgres://bolusi:bolusi@127.0.0.1:<port>/bolusi_dev
#   DATABASE_URL=$(pnpm -s db:url) pnpm dev:server
DATABASE_URL=
PORT=3000
# Blob storage root for assembled media (api/03-media §6; task 19). Server-local disk in v0;
# media is evidence and must persist — set an explicit, backed-up path in production.
MEDIA_STORAGE_DIR=
# OPTIONAL. Directory of per-tenant system-device signing keys (01 §3.6, 10-db §12) — the v0
# secret store that ENABLES conflict detection (01 §8.2). Point it at a directory holding the
# `system-device-<tenantId>.key` files `provision-tenant` writes (base64 Ed25519 secret). UNSET =
# conflict detection OFF (the honest default — pushes still succeed, no conflicts are detected).
# Set-but-broken (a missing/malformed/wrong-length key for a tenant with a real collision) fails
# LOUD, never silently off. Swap this file-dir mechanism for a KMS behind the same SystemKeyStore
# port without touching the pipeline (sync/system-key-store.ts).
SYSTEM_KEY_DIR=
